55.9	Richard_Saul_Wurman	Richard Saul Wurman	Richard Saul Wurman (March 26, 1935) is an architect and graphic designer who coined the phrase 'Information Architecture' and is considered to be a pioneer in the practice of making information easily understandable. Wurman has written and designed over 83 books, and created the TED conference, as well as the EG conference, TEDMED and the WWW suite of gatherings, now in development.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cb/Richard_Saul_Wurman2.jpg/220px-Richard_Saul_Wurman2.jpg
